main event: A DC-3 aircraft was mistaken for a UFO over Normal, Illinois on March 22, 1966.
interesting points: The DC-3 was making a low approach to land at the Bloomington-Normal airport, which led witnesses to mistake it for a UFO.
Witnesses described seeing an oblong object with blinking lights, which matched the lighting configuration of the DC-3.
The object was observed traveling at treetop level and making quick turns, which is consistent with the flight path of the descending DC-3.
Investigators were able to determine the exact time and location of the DC-3 flight, which correlated with the reported UFO sighting.
Witnesses' initial descriptions of the object being unusual and not a normal airplane were later contradicted when the DC-3 was identified as the source.
witnesses: Civilians, including a 15-year-old student and residents near the airport
